ZH: 我非常恼怒他的无礼行为。
EN: I am very angry with his rude behavior.

ZH: 他的无故迟到使老师非常恼怒。
EN: His unnecessary lateness made the teacher very angry.

ZH: 每次我看到他的脸，我都感到恼怒。
EN: Every time I see his face, I feel irritated.

ZH: 我父亲在开车时常常恼怒其他司机的不守规则。
EN: My father gets angry with other drivers who don't follow the rules when he's driving.

ZH: 她听到这个坏消息后，无法控制地恼怒起来。
EN: She couldn't help being furious after hearing the bad news.

ZH: 我感到恼怒的原因是他无视我的意见。
EN: The reason I'm angry is that he ignored my opinion.

ZH: 当时情况恼怒地超出了我的想象力。
EN: The situation was infuriatingly beyond my imagination.

ZH: 我不吃药的坚持让医生感到了恼怒。
EN: My refusal to take medicine made the doctor angry.

ZH: 她的冷淡态度激起了我的恼怒。
EN: Her cold attitude provoked my anger.

ZH: 这个服务员恼怒地对待了顾客。
EN: The waiter treated the customer angrily.

ZH: 恼怒的人很容易说出伤人的话。
EN: Angry people tend to say hurtful things.

ZH: 她恼怒地砸出一阵拳头。
EN: She angrily threw a punch.

