EN: Your words make me angry enough to want to leave.

ZH: 我们不应该因为一点小事而恼怒。
EN: We shouldn't get angry about trivial matters.

ZH: 他不停地重复同样的错误，让我感到恼怒。
EN: He keeps making the same mistake, which frustrates me.

